The paper discusses the use of deep learning for analyzing sports-related movements and predicting knee joint moments, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The study also involves motion capture and biomechanics, which could be categorized under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the practical application of the research for both community and professional level athletes, which could be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE).
